HEADWORD: Clergyman
<hw>Cler"gy*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Clergymen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <def>An ordained minister; a
man regularly authorized to preach the gospel, and administer its
ordinances; in England usually restricted to a minister of the
Established Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

